The paper focuses on robotics and machine learning, specifically on learning the dynamics of physical systems and predicting the effects of robot actions on articulated multi-part objects. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of graph neural networks and deep learning techniques, which are commonly associated with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of simulations and real-world experiments also suggests the possibility of cs.CV (Computer Vision) being a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the control and regulation of robot beliefs, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
